ï¼œBE:FIRST PROFILEï¼
BE:FIRST is a seven-member dance and vocal group featuring SOTA, SHUNTO, MANATO, RYUHEI, JUNON, RYOKI, and LEO, signed to a renowned Japanese rapper, SKY-HIâ€™s management agency and label BMSG. Each member possesses unique qualities for singing, dancing, and rapping, along with their musical agility reflected in their songwriting and choreography. Each owns an attractive individuality that marks them as unique. Under the name BE:FIRST, this seven-piece group has swept the No.1 spots on various charts in Japan since before their debut. Now they are taking the bold first steps from Tokyo to the world.

en-US.title: [Exciting] A close look at the first US tour - with broken English - [Part 2]
en-US.description:
The first half is here
https://youtu.be/NJUKR7copCo?si=_x1i3N02SSORWa0V

â–¼ Naomi Watanabe
https://www.instagram.com/watanabenaomi703/

This is the second part of my first all-English US tour, which took place in 2023, two years after I moved here! Sorry for the long wait since the first part! Lol

I learned a lot from this live show!

My English is really all messed up ğŸ˜‚ but thanks to the support of the customers who came to watch, I had fun and I had a lot of experiences, so this is a US tour I will never forget ğŸ¥¹

Rather than not doing anything until my English is perfect, I did the live show with the idea of â€‹â€‹moving forward as I go, but with my current learning ability, I will start moving when I'm about 100 years old ğŸ˜‚ It's too late lol ğŸ˜‚

I will continue to work hard on my English and keep moving forward! Thank you for your continued support ğŸ«¶

So, please look forward to the second part!

en.title: Part 2: My First U.S. Tour Documentary - Broken English Edition ã€2023ã€‘
en.description:
Hereâ€™s the second half of my first all-English U.S. tour in 2023, two years after moving here! Thanks for waiting sooo long since part one!

I learned so much from this tour! My English was honestly all over the place, but thanks to the incredible support from everyone who came to see the shows, I had an amazing time and gained so many unforgettable experiences. This U.S. tour will always be a special memory for me. ğŸ¥¹

Instead of waiting until my English was perfect, I chose to move forward while learning along the way. If I had waited until I mastered Englishâ€¦ well, at my pace, Iâ€™d probably be ready to start performing at around 100 years old! ğŸ˜‚ Way too slow, right? 

Iâ€™ll keep working hard on my English and pushing forward! Thank you always for your support! ğŸ«¶

Hope you enjoy part two!

snippet.title: NOBODY Expected This Japanese Guy to Speak Every Language!
snippet.description:
â—Instagram: @kazulanguages - https://www.instagram.com/kazulanguages/
â—Buy me a coffee: https://www.buymeacoffee.com/kazulanguages
â—TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@kazulanguages

This video is a mix of OmeTV and Tokyo! Japanese polyglot spoke 18 languages but nobody expected me to speak every language! So many wholesome reactions in this video! I also met a famous Aussie actor in Tokyo, which was an incredibly memory.
Currently, I speak 14 languages, which I studied properly. These are English, Spanish, French, Portuguese, Arabic, Indonesian, Russian, Hindi, German, Turkish, Chinese, Thai, Korean, Polish and Dutch. And now I'm learning Greek, Tagalog, Cantonese, and Italian! Apart from that, I speak Japanese for sure, which is my native language.
Furthermore, I know a tiny bit of Italian, Swedish, Romanian, Farsi, Swahili, Tagalog, Burmese, Geogian, Finnish, Uzbek, Kazakh and Bengali!
Of course, my skills of these languages are still far from sufficient.
The thing I value the most, however, is the attitude to trying to know their culture.
Interacting with people from different background is an eye-opening experience and that makes me really happy.
I wanna inspire people to learn different languages.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[ Timestamps ]  

00:00 - Intro
00:31 - (Finnish) They freaked out when I spoke her language
01:44 - (Bosnian) Funniest Reaction Ever! I surprised them 4 times!
05:17 - (Turkish) She got blackout when I spoke her native language!
06:57 - (Greek) They smiled as soon as I spoke Greek
07:36 - (Kazakh) I pranked them by speaking languages!
09:50 - (Dutch) This Polyglot girl surprised me and I surprised her!
13:24 - (Spanish) Famous Aussie actor, Les Hill shocked me!
15:33 - (Multilingual) Heartwarming conversation in multiple languages!
17:47 - (Russian) Wholesome encounter! Making friends with foreigners in an instant!
22:54 - Outro


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

And now I'm learning Greek, Tagalog, Cantonese, and Italian! Apart from that, I speak Japanese for sure, which is my native language.
Furthermore, I know a tiny bit of Italian, Swedish, Romanian, Farsi, Swahili, Tagalog, Burmese, Geogian, Finnish, Uzbek, Kazakh and Bengali!
Of course, my skills of these languages are still far from sufficient.
The thing I value the most, however, is the attitude to trying to know their culture.
Interacting with people from different background is an eye-opening experience and that makes me really happy.
I wanna inspire people to learn different languages.

en-US.title: We got married!
en-US.description:
Furukawa Yuka is getting married!

I will be becoming husband and wife with my beloved Saguwa-kun, who has always supported me.
I hope we can continue to have fun, even as we fight about silly things.

And I have one more thing to announce.
We have been blessed with a new life.

Together with Saguwa-kun and our beloved dog Fuku-chan,
we hope to live a lively life as a family of four.

Thank you so much to everyone who supports us.
We are a laid-back bunch, but we hope you will continue to support us!

2025.03.15
